reviewText: It's Law & Order-SVU: The 16th Year. Nothing more to say than "well worth the watch".

The 16th Season of Law & Order returning to the crime scene with 22 episodes!! Also returning to the 16th season are S.Epatha Merkerson, Sam Waterston, Jesse L. Martin, and Fred Dalton Thompson. After 2 seasons, 47 episodes, the late Dennis Farina returns in his final season as Detective Joe Fontana. Also there's a crossover episode between Law & Order and Law & Order:SVU. The 1st part starts off on Law & Order:SVU, and it ends on the 2nd part on Law & Order.

I really like this season. It had a varied mix of stories. It also had Dennis Farina. I always liked him. He had a natural way of acting. I really liked the chemistry between him and Martin. They complimented each other. The reason I like this installment was because people forget he was a real police officer. So when you see him you see how to correctly hold a gun, interrogate a suspect/witness, pursue someone, etc. There are some liberties that are taken on this segment but it helps to ground the series.

Update: Overall this was a good year with a few not so well written episodes so I'm upping my rating to a four star form a 2 star.
